Background

Summary

I'm a technology junkie and have been using computers since my early teens. I love problem solving and making a difference to the world, which is why I chose to become a software developer.

Currently I'm a web developer at Founders and Coders academy where I helped build a clone version of the social networking website Twitter using Node.js complete with location based tweeting. Before applying to join the highly sought-after coding course at Founders and Coders I was a qualified teacher of ICT. I have extensive teaching experience at various levels and my most recent teaching assignment was in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia where I taught ICT and Mathematics.

If you were to ask my friends and colleagues about me, I think they would describe me as someone who is a go-getter, honest, loyal and hard working. Over the years I have worked with incredibly smart and experienced individuals and this has taught me how to work collaboratively with others to produce results of the highest quality.

I have a BEng in Computer Systems from the University of Greenwich and a PGCE from Middlesex University. However, I believe that education is continuous and that is why I constantly strive to keep my knowledge and skills up-to-date in the ever changing world of the 21st century that we live in.

I'm currently freelancing with Founders and Coders and if you have any interesting projects that you would like me to work on with you, then you can reach out to me through my profile.
